The paper also deals with image-related tasks such as image classification, image-to-image translation, and attribute-based image generation. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper involves the use of neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the use of adversarial learning, which is a technique used in both machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of discriminators to distinguish between real and fake data pairs, which is a graph-related task. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
